This Privacy Policy is offered by
Showpad Inc
, a Delaware company with address 1 N. State St., Suite #1100 (11th Floor), Chicago, IL 60602 (USA) (company ID 5314227) for data subjects located within the Americas, Australia & New-Zealand; and
Showpad NV
, Moutstraat 62, 9000 Gent (Belgium) (company ID 836.159.992 – RPR Gent) for data subjects located within the rest of the world. (“Showpad”)
This Privacy Policy applies
in the situations whereby Showpad:
is processing information which relates to You (as being an identified or identifiable natural person) (“Personal Data”);
for which Showpad determines the purposes and means of processing (as being data “Controller”); and
for such purposes as specifically set forth in section A.2 below.
This Privacy Policy does
NOT
apply
to Your use of, or interaction with the Showpad SaaS Products and Services (“Product and Services), or content managed thereon, unless:
One or more of the purposes as set forth in this Privacy Policy
specifically
apply to Your Interaction (see A.2 below); or
Content belonging to, or controlled by Showpad (or one of its affiliates) is being made available to You by an employee or agent of Showpad (or one of its affiliates) through the Product and Services for Showpad’s own business purpose.
This privacy Policy consists out of 2 parts:
1. Privacy Policy /2. Cookie Policy.
We may change this Privacy Policy
at any time, and all such changes are effective immediately upon posting a revised version of this Privacy Policy on the Website. You should review this Privacy Policy often to stay informed of changes that may affect You. Your Interactions constitute Your continuing agreement to be bound by this Privacy Policy, as they are amended from time to time.
Where this Privacy Policy does not apply
, please check the Showpad privacy principles at
www.showpad.com/gdpr/
for their applicability.
A. Privacy Policy
1. Preamble
As a company that finds its roots in the European Union, and that considers compliance to privacy legislation Privacy a core principles of its organisation, Showpad has created this Privacy Policy based upon the foundations of the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) (Regulation (EU) 2016/679 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 27 April 2016 on the protection of natural persons with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data).
As GDPR currently is the most advanced and elaborate data protection law in the world, Showpad uses GDPR as its main benchmark for its companywide privacy program.
Seeing the global activities of Showpad, it goes without saying that with this Privacy Policy, in addition to GDPR, Showpad also wants to take into account the principles of other applicable data protection laws, which principles are either already incorporated through GDPR (in most of the cases) or either have specifically been added to this Privacy Policy.
2. What "Interactions" trigger this Privacy Policy to be applicable?
The following interactions (“Interactions”) will make this Privacy Policy to become applicable:
Your use of and/or interaction with any website (other than the Showpad Saas Product)  i) belonging to the Showpad.com domain (i.e. the Showpad commercial website), ii) managed by Showpad, iii) referring to any of the foregoing, or iv) operated by a third-party on behalf of Showpad (“Website”);
Your use of any content belonging to, or controlled by Showpad, as being made available to You by an employee or agent of Showpad, including via the Showpad Product and Services;
Your use of the Showpad Product and Services under an Administrator account or where there is a specific mention related to the Showpad Product and Services under the purposes below (see A.3);
Direct Interactions with Showpad (e.g. certain sales and/or marketing interactions, face-to-face meetings, interactions at exhibitions, sales pitches, commercial gatherings, training session, providing feedback, webinars, social media interactions, events, email inquiries, interactions with Showpad through the Showpad Sales enablement Solution, job searches, …);
Interactions (with (software) tools) related to the foregoing (e.g. direct marketing tools, job applications tools, Net Promotor Scoring (NPS), account registrations, support, etc.); and/or
Explicit acceptance of this Privacy Policy.
Be aware that the applicability of this Privacy Policy following your Interactions will be for the specific purpose (see A3) for which Your Personal Data is being processed by Showpad.
3. For what purposes and under what legal grounds do we process your personal data?
Showpad may (be required to) process certain Personal Data for one or more of the following purposes:
Contract administration
