3.7 Online Meetings
We use Zoom to conduct online meetings, video conferences and/or online training (hereinafter referred to as “Zoom Meetings”). “Zoom” is a service of Zoom Video Communications, Inc., which is based in the United States. Where the Zoom meeting is (to be) recorded, you may be informed via the Zoom functionality which ask for your consent. We use recordings of Zoom meetings for purpose of documentation and training (see further in our privacy policy). By participating in Zoom meetings, you consent to the collection, processing, and disclosure of information as described in this Privacy Policy.
As a result of participating in the Zoom Meeting, we may be processing the following information:
Personal Information: Your name, email address, and other information you provide when joining a Zoom meeting.
Meeting Content: Any data, including video, audio, and chat content, generated during the Zoom meeting.
Technical Information: Information about your device, network, and Zoom usage, including IP address, device information, and connection logs.
Apart from supporting any of the other purposes mentioned in the privacy policy, we use information processed during Zoom meetings for the following purposes:
Meeting Facilitation: To facilitate and manage Zoom Meetings, including participant authentication and communication.
Meeting Analytics: To analyse usage patterns, troubleshoot issues, and improve the quality of our Zoom meetings.
Security: To ensure the security and integrity of Zoom meetings, including detecting and preventing unauthorised access or misuse.
To the extent required to inform You per applicable Data Protection law, Processing of Personal Data for this Purpose is based upon the following legal grounds:
where the data subject “
has given consent to the processing of his or her Personal Data for one or more specific purposes
”; and/or
“
processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which the data subject is party
“ or “
in order to take steps at the request of the data subject prior to entering into a contract”
; and/or
“processing is necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the controller”
, (e.g. in case there is no contractual relationship or negotiation thereto and more specifically the fact that Showpad is i) pursuing business development and/or expansion and maintenance of (commercial) relationships with customers as well as other third parties and ii) ensuring business operations in general, handling files relating to Showpad’s core business with intervening third parties, maintaining good relationships with suppliers, working on business projects with third parties, etc.
The Processing of this Personal Data is an absolute requirement. You not allowing us to process (all or some of) this Personal Data this Personal Data for this purpose may mean that You may not be allowed to participate in said Zoom Meeting.
Be aware that this purpose is in addition to and leaves unharmed any other purpose as per this Privacy Policy.
